Introduction In case you are just tuning in, Doyensec has found themselves on a cruse ship touring the Mediterranean. Unwinding, hanging out with colleagues and having some fun. Part 1 covered our journey into IoT ARM exploitation, while our next blog post, coming in the next couple weeks, will cover a web target. For this episode, we attempt to exploit one of the most famous vulnerabilities ever. SSHNuke from back in 2001. Better known as the exploit used by Trinity in the movie The Matrix Reloaded.
